Project Brief & PRD: Avemaría Villavicencio Landing Page

1. Project Overview

Client: Avemaría Villavicencio
Location: Villavicencio, Colombia
Project Type: High-Conversion Landing Page (Mobile-First)
Primary Goal: Generate reservations, event inquiries, and visits via WhatsApp, digital menu access, and local SEO.

2. Strategic Objectives





Positioning: Establish Avemaría as a premium, natural, "outdoor experience" destination in Villavicencio, moving beyond just "food" to "gastronomic plan."



Conversion (CRO): Minimize the path to action. Users should be able to book, view the menu, or get directions in under 60 seconds.



Trust & Reputation: Leverage social proof (reviews) and clear operational data (FAQ, location) to build visitor confidence.



Local SEO: Rank for high-intent keywords like "restaurante al aire libre Villavicencio" and "parrilla Villavicencio."

3. Target Audience





Local Families: Looking for a safe, natural space for weekend plans.



Groups & Friends: Seeking a comfortable outdoor environment for celebrations.



Couples: Looking for a scenic, premium atmosphere for dates.



Event Planners: Individuals seeking venues for birthdays or small corporate gatherings.

4. Information Architecture & UX Structure

Core Sections:





Hero Section: High-impact visual with immediate CTAs (WhatsApp, Menu, Maps).



Quick Action Bar (Mobile): Sticky footer for persistent access to critical functions.



The Experience: Emotional storytelling focusing on Nature, Grill, Family, and Atmosphere.



Digital Menu: Visual category-based preview (Grill, Main Courses, Drinks, etc.) without heavy PDF dependency.



Events & Celebrations: Dedicated lead capture for high-ticket bookings.



Social Proof: Integrated Google/Tripadvisor reviews.



Location & Operations: Map integration, address, and verified hours.



FAQ: Pre-empting common queries (Pet-friendly, Parking, Payment).

5. Visual Identity (Organic Gourmet Narrative)





Palette: Deep Forest Green (#1b3022), Warm Earth/Terracotta, Creams, and Soft Gold.



Typography: Elegant Serifs (Playfair Display) for headlines; Modern Sans-Serifs for readability.



Style: Premium but approachable; organic textures (wood, fire, greenery).



Tone of Voice: Warm, gastronomic, professional, and inviting.

6. Functional Requirements





WhatsApp Integration: Dynamic links with pre-filled intent-based messages (Reservation vs. Event vs. Menu).



Responsive Design: Mobile-first approach with desktop-optimized views.



SEO Optimization: Correct H1-H3 hierarchy, meta-descriptions, and LocalBusiness Schema preparation.



Analytics Ready: Tracking for WhatsApp clicks, menu views, and scroll depth.

7. Operational Constraints & Continuity





Data Integrity: No unconfirmed claims. Missing data is marked as "Pendiente por confirmar" to ensure brand honesty.



Language: Spanish-first content for local market alignment.

8. Success Metrics (KPIs)





Primary: Total clicks on WhatsApp Reservation buttons.



Secondary: Map directions clicks, digital menu views, and event inquiry volume.